# QoS Classes

Computed from resources (you don't set it). Decides **eviction order**.

| Class | Qualifies |
|---|---|
| **Guaranteed** | every container: CPU+mem, **requests == limits** |
| **Burstable** | some request/limit, not Guaranteed (80%) |
| **BestEffort** | **no** requests/limits at all |

## Eviction under memory pressure

> **BestEffort** → **Burstable** (over requests) → **Guaranteed** last.

> Cheapest insurance: **`requests == limits` on memory** → Guaranteed → left alone.

## OOMKilled vs Evicted

- **OOMKilled** — one **container** over its **limit**; kernel kills it. `restartCount`↑. Fix: **raise limit / fix leak.**
- **Evicted** — whole **Pod** off a pressured **node**. Phase `Failed`. Fix: **set requests / scale.**

> `kubectl describe pod` tells you which.
